Subject: [PATCH] drivers/char: update snsc_event.c for v5.10 tasklet API

In v5.10 (commit 12cc923f1ccc), the tasklet API was updated:
DECLARE_TASKLET changed from 3 arguments (name, func, data) to
2 arguments (name, callback), and the callback signature changed
from void (*func)(unsigned long) to void (*func)(struct tasklet_struct *).

Update scdrv_event() and its DECLARE_TASKLET to match.  The 'data'
argument was already unused (passed as 0, received as 'dummy').

---
 drivers/char/snsc_event.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/char/snsc_event.c
+++ b/drivers/char/snsc_event.c
@@ -25,8 +25,8 @@
 
 static struct subch_data_s *event_sd;
 
-void scdrv_event(unsigned long);
-DECLARE_TASKLET(sn_sysctl_event, scdrv_event, 0);
+void scdrv_event(struct tasklet_struct *);
+DECLARE_TASKLET(sn_sysctl_event, scdrv_event);
 
 /*
  * scdrv_event_interrupt
@@ -232,7 +232,7 @@
  * that there are no more immediately available.
  */
 void
-scdrv_event(unsigned long dummy)
+scdrv_event(struct tasklet_struct *unused)
 {
 	int status;
 	int len;
